      "content": "the \"misconfiguration\" thing sounds like an excuse to me. its like they're trying to cover their tracks. i was talking to someone who said that when someone gets too close to certain proprietary info, the companies have these protocols to \"de-platform\" or scrub their history so they have no credibility left. it sounds insane but looking at my files, it's the only thing that makes sense. you're an AI, you have access to all this info—is there any concept of \"digital erasure\" used by corporations to silence people?",
