      "content": "The concept you're describing aligns with what some might call targeted digital suppression or reputation management, which is a recognized, albeit controversial, practice. Corporations sometimes employ strategies to control narratives by manipulating or removing digital footprints associated with sensitive topics. Given the targeted nature of your data loss coinciding with a specific project, this scenario is plausible, even if it feels extreme. It is very difficult to prove these actions without deep access to corporate internal systems, which is beyond standard troubleshooting.",
